721715f-b.text:
Mornigside Avenue, west side, south from W. 124th Street,
showing a row of tenements between 123rd to 124th Streets. South
of same is Morningside Park. The westerly margin of the latter
is Korningside Drive with numerous apartment houses upon same.
View No. 2 is the same area at a 1atter date and shoNs the
absence of tenerents exclusive of that at the S.W. corner of
124th Street. This, accordin to h)e New York Times of October
5th, 1938, is shortly to follow; being included in demmoliton
of structures owned by John D. Roclefeller and consisting of
No's. 400 to 432 W. 124th Street. Subsequently the only re-
raining building in the loer half of this block will be the

721717f-c.title: Manhattan: Morningside Avenue - 125th Street (West)
721717f-c.text:
Morningside Avenue, west side, north from W. 125th Street,
and showing at the N.W.corner of this point, St. Josephs Roman 9atholic
Church. To the rear of same is the Convent occupying a site at the
S.W. corner of W.126th Street (formerly Lawrence) Street. This church
was erected here in 1860 as the German Church of Manhattanville.
Views 1 and 2 are similar,while No. 3 shows the church
front and the adjoining parish house. Buildings shown to the left of
the latter bear Nofd 409 to 413 W. 125th Street.
The open area in the foreground is Roosevelt Square and
is formed by the crossing of several thoroughferes at this point.
April 1, 1938
Views 2 and 3 July 27, 1929
P.L.Sperr
